$
  A DATASET IS QUEUED FOR LATER ARCHIVE PROCESSING THROUGH THE ASM2 TSO
  COMMAND.  AN SPF INTERFACE HAS BEEN PROVIDED TO SIMPLIFY USE OF THIS COMMAND.

  A DATASET IS QUEUED FOR ARCHIVING BY SELECTING OPTION&A$ON THE &ASM2 ARCHIVE
  UTILITY$MENU.  ENTER THE NAME OF THE DATASET TO BE ARCHIVED IN THE&NAME$AREA.
  NORMAL TSO NAMING CONVENTIONS APPLY.  USE SINGLE QUOTES&(')$FOR FULLY
  QUALIFIED NAMES.

  YOU MAY SPECIFY THE NUMBER OF DAYS THE ARCHIVED DATASET SHOULD BE KEPT IN
  THE&RETENTION$FIELD.  NOTE:  DEFAULTS ARE&365 (1 YR.)$FOR &NORMAL
  ARCHIVES$,AND&1825 (5 YR.)&FOR PERMANENT ARCHIVES$. A RETENTION GREATER
  THAN&3 YEARS$IS AUTOMATICALLY CONSIDERED PERMANENT.  YOU MAY CLASSIFY AN
  ARCHIVE REQUEST AS PERMANENT,  REGARDLESS OF THE RETENTION PERIOD,  BY CODING
  A&Y$ IN THE&PERMANENT ARCHIVE$FIELD.

